# Markdown Rules

## File Organization
Prefer only this repo’s `README.md` for markdown docs. Do not invent extra guides.

(Product tracker / ARCHITECTURE / DEPLOYMENT live in the sibling backend repo — leave those alone from frontend work unless the user asks.)

## Documentation Updates
- **NEVER automatically update README files when code changes**
- Always ask first: "Should I update the README to reflect this change?"
- Only update after explicit confirmation

## Content Guidelines

### README.md
- How to run locally
- Start/stop commands
- Project structure
- Key commands (`npm run dev`, build, lint)

## Formatting
- ATX-style headers (# ## ###)
- One blank line between sections
- Code blocks with language: ```ts
- Lists: `-` for unordered, `1.` for ordered
- Keep it scannable and concise
